<%= content_for :head do %>
  <%= javascript_import_module_tag "example" %>
<% end %>

<% if user_signed_in? %>
  <div class="jumbotron jumbotron-fluid">
    <div class="container">
    <h1>Welcome back!</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
<% else %>
  <div class="jumbotron jumbotron-fluid">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>&#128248 Welcome to Pixel Playground! &#127752</h1>
      <p>This is a template for a simple marketing or informational website.
      It includes a large callout called a jumbotron and three supporting
      pieces of of content. Use it as a starting point to create something
      unique</p>
      <%= link_to "Learn More", "http://www.yahoo.com.sg", target: "_blank", class: "btn btn-primary btn-md" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container d-flex justify-content-center">
    <div class="row gy-5">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100" style="width: 18rem;">
          <img class="card-img-top" src="<%= asset_path('family.jpg')%>" alt="Card image">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="card-title">Family 🏡</h3>
            <p class="card-text">Oh yes! I am married with my lovely wife and blessed with 3 awesome kids!
            My life evolves around them and gone are the days of spending countless hours outside
            with my homies. Parenthood taught me patience, lots of it...! dedication and
            a deep sense of responsibility.😁 </p>
            <div class="button-home fixed-bottom">
              <%= link_to "View details", "#", class: "btn btn-secondary home" %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100" style="width: 18rem;">
          <img class="card-img-top" src="<%= asset_path('leisure.jpg')%>" alt="Card image">
          <div class="card-body ">
            <h3 class="card-title">Leisure 🏖</h3>
            <p class="card-text">This is almost non-existence! Ok I'm exxagerating it. But really, before
            marriage existed, any random day could be a leisure day. Not anymore. LOL. Waiting for the
            weekend is like preparing a tasty meal that takes hours to cook and minutes to consume. Lots of plan
            but just so little time! 🤣 </p>
            <div class="button-home fixed-bottom">
              <%= link_to "View details", "#", class: "btn btn-secondary home" %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100" style="width: 18rem;">
          <img class="card-img-top" src="<%= asset_path('coding.jpg')%>" alt="Card image">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="card-title">Coding ⚙</h3>
            <p class="card-text">Yes, you guessed it right. So where in the world do I get the time to code?
            Its a struggle my friend. 😥 Juggling with work, family (running & shouting kids included) and
            trying my very best to watch coding tutorials and attending a part-time bootcamp which I have
            graduated recently. </p>
            <div class="button-home fixed-bottom">
              <%= link_to "View details", "#", class: "btn btn-secondary home" %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
<% end %>
